# Zero AI attribution in git history

This repository forbids any `Co-authored-by` trailers that attribute commits to AI.

**Rules:**
- NEVER add `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>` to any commit message, PR description, or patch.
- NEVER add `Co-authored-by: Claude`, `Co-authored-by: ChatGPT`, `Co-authored-by: Copilot`, or any other AI assistant trailer.
- Commits must be attributed ONLY to the human author (e.g. `Travis Vocino <travis@vocino.com>`).
- If any tool auto-injects a co-author line, you MUST strip it before finalizing the commit.
- When generating a commit message suggestion, output ONLY the clean conventional commit (type, scope, body) with no footer attribution.
- The same applies to PR bodies and commit-msg hooks — do not add attribution.

**Why:** Keep git history clean and human-attributed. No AI branding in the public GitHub log.

**If you see a hook or tool trying to add it, disable it immediately.**
